This paper focuses on the detection of fake news by assessing its credibility, which involves analyzing news sources and authors. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes research on natural language processing and information retrieval. The paper also involves analyzing public data, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the role of authors in detecting fake news, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
